ADOPTION INFORMATION: 
All animals adopted from The SPCA of Monterey County are spayed or neutered prior to adoption and have received vaccinations appropriate to age and species, permanent microchip identification, SPCA identification tag, health evaluations, behavior evaluations (for dogs) and more! Please note that in order to make the best match possible, potential adopters must come to The SPCA of Monterey County in person to meet with an adoption counselor and complete the adoption process. All members of the household (including other pets, if applicable) should be present to ensure the chosen pet is compatible with everyone. For the health and safety of our animals we do not place holds or do adoptions over the phone and we do not ship pets.
 
For more information on the adoption process please visit  http://www.SPCAmc.org.
 ADOPTION HOURS: 
Monday - Friday: 11 A.M. TO 5 P.M.
 Saturday - Sunday: 11 A.M. TO 4 P.M.
 
1002 Highway 68
 Across from Mazda Raceway at Laguna Seca
 
(831) 373-2631 or 422-4721

Please watch a short video of the puppies below: These babies will be available beginning on Fri, 9/29/17. They will need experienced adopters to guide them into successful adulthoods. They are currently recovering from a cold which could be potentially contagious to other dogs for several weeks after recovery. Prospective adopters will need to complete applications and be pre-screened prior to meeting the pups. Submitting an application does not guarantee a meeting with the pups, nor does it obligate the applicant in any way.  Applications can be downloaded here: http://scanimalshelter.org/adoption_application. Completed applications can be turned in to the Santa Cruz branch of the shelter during business hours or scanned and emailed to asa143@santacruzcounty.us   .  More information about our adoption process can be seen here: http://scanimalshelter.org/adoption_process    Please consider supporting local animals (PayPal button below):        safer, easier way to pay online!>

The Santa Cruz SPCA is an independent 501(c)3 non-profit organization dedicated to the welfare of animals. Our organization, and the work that we do, is supported by individual contributions.

All of our adoptions include spay/neuter, microchip, recent treatment for fleas and worms, age appropriate vaccinations, testing for FELV/FIV, certificate for free vet exam and an adoption packet with additional pet care information and coupons. Please visit our website for adoption procedures. www.spcasc.org

Puppies (under 1 year of age); $300.00
Adult Dogs (1-7 years); $200.00
Senior Dogs (8+) $150.00

Angelina is a little lady. She is initially a bit shy with strangers but like all puppies she wants to be cuddled and loved. She is a serious girl and a good listener. She likes other dogs and is curious about the world around her. She is very smart and will probably be easily trained. She is quiet and thoughtful. She likes to sit back and watch before making that leap!

Burt is very healthy, adorable well socialized little puppy, he along with his siblings all have their own individual personalities.

Daisy Two came to us from Hollister Animal Shelter. She was surrendered due to people moving. Daisy did not have much of a prior life, it was spent in a crate, no daily walks, no socialization, no toys, and zero vet care. So very sad. 

Today, Daisy's story is one of progress, she is alert, very loving, plays with toys and with the two cats in her foster home. Her foster Mum said she is so sweet and an undemanding little puppy, who enjoys sitting on your lap. No pun intended, she laps up all the attention she can get, who can blame her after being deprived. 

Look at her soulful sweet little face. She will make a wonderful companion to a family/person.

Domino is one of the four daughters of Abacus. She is more streamlined than her sisters and seemingly the smartest one of all four. She is delightful, has a fun personality and is very outgoing. She will not be ready to go to her new home until September 24, 2017.

Maude is one of the four daughters of Abacus. She is a chunky little mixed breed girl who is smart, has a delightful personality and is outgoing and fun. She will not be ready to go to her new home until September 24, 2017.

Sweet Harry! This little guy came to us after his mom and siblings were turned into the shelter. The good Samaritan who brought them in said he found them huddled together next to a creek. His foster mom knew his name the moment she laid eyes on him! He is so FLUFFY and is such a social little guy. He is always ready to play or just cuddle. He is easy going in nature, and he truly gets along great with everyone.
Ebony is a spunky puppy full of energy and fun.  He loves to wrestle and play with his two puppy siblings.  He's well mannered in the house and very sweet.

Ivory is a very shy puppy that is still learning that humans can be nice.  When she came to our rescue she was afraid of everyone but has come a long way since then.  She loves to play with other dogs and is very well behaved and quiet.

Miss Ivory is as much like a cat as a dog. We don't know what happened in her earlier life to make her timid but if she learns to trust you and you are sitting quietly, she will come near for stroking and even sometimes turn up her silky soft tummy for a rub. Like cats, she prefers that all encounters be on her terms, and like cats, her satin soft warm body is worth waiting for. So if you like little dogs that aren't always in your face, and you also like cats, Miss Ivory may be the perfect companion for you.
Molly is from a litter of 6 puppies.  She is proving to be the sassy one who likes to sneak up on her sleeping siblings and pounce to play.  She pouts when she doesn't get her way.  Adorable sweetie!
Rocky is from a litter of six puppies.  Rocky is proving to be the baby.  He needs attention and will let you know it.  He likes to get up on his hind legs and box.  He is also quite a snuggler.

Foxey is from a litter of six puppies.  She is the quiet watcher and very curious of everything.  She likes to have her ears scratched and will lick your hands as a thank you.  She also likes to cuddle with a stuffed animal friend.
Rubble is from a litter of six puppies.  Rubble is the love-bug of the group.  he prefers to sleep close and under your shirt or a blanket next to you.  He is very laid back.

Max is from a litter of six puppies.  He is proving to be the one with the most energy.  He is constantly on the move and getting into everything.  He likes to play with the bigger dogs in the foster home and playing tug of war.

Millie is from a litter of six puppies.  Millie is an "old soul".  She's sweet and cuddly and just watches over all of her siblings.  She enjoys cuddling but gets a little nervous when she's alone.  Loves being around stuffed animals.
